io.codecastle.scriptorium.json

Class JsonKey<P>

  • Object
    • JsonKey<P>
  • Type Parameters:
    P - the type of the containing JsonObject
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    FluentAppendable<JsonKey<P>>, Inscribable<JsonAppendable<?>,JsonKey<P>>, JsonAppendable<JsonKey<P>>, Appendable

    public final class JsonKey<P>
extends Object
    Represents a JSON key currently being output within a containing JsonObject.
    See Also:
    JsonObject.key()

    • Method Detail

      • value

        public JsonValue<P> value()
                   throws IOException
        Closes this JSON key, then begins a new string literal value assigned to it and returns a JsonValue that can be used to assign characters to it.

        Calling the JsonValue.then() method of the returned JsonValue will return the JsonObject that contains this key.

        Calling any method of this object's parent before closing the returned JsonValue may result in invalid output and/or an unchecked exception.

        When this method returns, a closing quote, colon, and opening quote will have already been appended to the underlying Appendable.

        Returns:
        a JsonValue representing a new string literal value assigned to this key
        Throws:
        IOException - if an I/O error occurs
        See Also:
        JsonValue, value(char), value(Character), value(CharSequence)

      • value

        public JsonValue<P> value(char value)
                   throws IOException
        Closes this JSON key, then begins a new string literal value assigned to it, beginning with the provided character, and returns a JsonValue that can be used to assign characters to it.

        Calling the JsonValue.then() method of the returned JsonValue will return the JsonObject that contains this key.

        Calling any method of this object's parent before closing the returned JsonValue may result in invalid output and/or an unchecked exception.

        The provided character will be escaped.

        When this method returns, a closing quote, colon, opening quote, and the provided character will have already been appended to the underlying Appendable.

        Parameters:
        value - the first character of the new string literal value
        Returns:
        a JsonValue representing a new string literal value assigned to this key
        Throws:
        IOException - if an I/O error occurs
        See Also:
        JsonValue, value(), value(char), value(CharSequence)

      • value

        public JsonValue<P> value(Character value)
                   throws IOException
        Closes this JSON key, then begins a new string literal value assigned to it, beginning with the provided Character, and returns a JsonValue that can be used to assign characters to it.

        Calling the JsonValue.then() method of the returned JsonValue will return the JsonObject that contains this key.

        Calling any method of this object's parent before closing the returned JsonValue may result in invalid output and/or an unchecked exception.

        The provided character will be escaped.

        If the provided character is null, nothing will be prepended to the value. I.e., when this method returns only a closing quote, colon, and opening quote will be appended to the underlying Appendable

        Parameters:
        value - the first character of the new string literal value
        Returns:
        a JsonValue representing a new string literal value assigned to this key
        Throws:
        IOException - if an I/O error occurs
        See Also:
        JsonValue, value(), value(char), value(CharSequence)

      • value

        public JsonValue<P> value(CharSequence value)
                   throws IOException
        Closes this JSON key, then begins a new string literal value assigned to it, beginning with the provided CharSequence, and returns a JsonValue that can be used to assign characters to it.

        Calling the JsonValue.then() method of the returned JsonValue will return the JsonObject that contains this key.

        Calling any method of this object's parent before closing the returned JsonValue may result in invalid output and/or an unchecked exception.

        The contents of the provided CharSequence will be escaped.

        If the provided CharSequence is null, nothing will be prepended to the value. I.e., when this method returns only a closing quote, colon, and opening quote will be appended to the underlying Appendable

        Parameters:
        value - the beginning characters of the new string literal value
        Returns:
        a JsonValue representing a new string literal value assigned to this key
        Throws:
        IOException - if an I/O error occurs
        See Also:
        JsonValue, value(), value(char), value(Character)

        public THIS append(CharSequence sequence,
                   int start,
                   int end)
            throws IOException
        Description copied from interface: JsonAppendable
        Appends the specified subsequence of the provided CharSequence and returns this object.

        The provided characters will be escaped.

        This method differs from Appendable.append(CharSequence, int, int): if the provided sequence is null or if start is less than zero or end is less than or equal to start, this method has no effect.

        Description copied from interface: io.codecastle.scriptorium.Inscribable
        Inscribes another FluentNode in this object, and returns it.

        This method calls the provided function, passing this object as the input, and returns the output.
